Reference-contexts: and facilitate the replacement of the PLP analysis with other feature extractors such as LPC which do not involve a FFT, the DC-component removal unit was imple mented using a simple first-order IIR filter. * Signal Representation: The speech signal is represented using a seventh-order PLP (Perceptual Linear Predictive) analysis <ref> [5] </ref> every 10ms using a 10ms window. This analysis yields eight coefficients per frame (7 cep-stral coefficients and one energy coefficient). * Pre-normalization: The energy coefficient of the input cepstral feature vector is normalized using an automatic gain control filter (AGC), with a look-ahead buffer of 160ms.
