Reference-contexts: Regarding Modularity The philosophy behind the real-time implementation was to maintain modularity of run-time code throughout the whole recognition process. Maintaining modularity allows rapid future development of related algorithms. Using the VCOS <ref> [6] </ref> operating environment we were able to efficiently develop stand-alone DSP modules with input, output and parameter buffers. VCOS provides an environment where one can reuse these modules in an application without referring to the assembly code.
